You can carry de-cocked, pull and fire like a double action revolver the first shot and then following shots are short single action. This is a very safe handgun. Face to face transactions. postcontent:
June 8th
Approx 5 miles south of Erie
15550 Hwy 47 - contact me for exact directions

Class starts at 8:00 AM.
Class size is typically limited to the first 50 individuals
Please contact me to register before but walk-ins are welcome
Cost is $65 - Cash or Checks accepted
Hamburgers, Hot dogs and other items will be available for purchase for lunch

The Kansas Concealed Carry Handgun (CCH) course is a mandatory eight hour course that is taught within the parameters set forth by the Kansas Attorney General. The course entails instruction in basic firearms safety, marksmanship, Kansas law as it pertains to CCH, and situational scenarios that a CCH licensee must be made aware of. The course of fire is designed to accommodate all levels of shooters (beginner through expert). The student must score 100% on a written test over discussion material, and must score 18 out of 25 during the shooting qualification. You don't need to worry about either test as you will be given everything you will need to pass them both during the 8 hour course. 

Please bring your own pistol along with 50 rounds of ammunition for the shooting portion.  Also bring along eye and hearing protection as these are required while shooting.
